2.1.2 One-Dimensional Diatomic Chain

A 1D chain establishes the basic principles of the dispersion of lattice vibrations in solids, but of course a monatomic chain cannot be turned into a ferroelectric. To explain the microscopic physics behind ferroelectricity, we need at least two atoms in a unit cell, and we will brieï¬‚y sketch the general principles of the diatomic chain.
