(b)
(c)
That is, the polarization is proportional to L; P/Np0 = L. The long-range order parameter is therefore very signiï¬cant for the permanent dipole ferroelectrics, because in these materials there must exist a â€œspontaneousâ€ long-range order.
The parameter L takes values from zero at complete disorder to unity at complete order. The condition L = âˆ’1 is another state of complete order, corresponding to P = âˆ’Np0. The condition L = 1 corresponds to n = N, all dipoles being aligned. In the other state of complete order, L = âˆ’1, all dipoles pointing in the opposite direction. Figure 2.16a,b each represents a state of complete order. The condition of complete disorder, L = 0, corresponds to n = 1 N, in which half
